<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.6321/86</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Penfield</persName>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1305. Your 1339, July 17, 11 a.m. Department not entirely clear
                                respecting meaning Foreign Office note. Mail copy as soon as
                                possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>